            <section class="w-100" id="citation-container">
                    <div class="container">
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Benzene ring</b>- a bonded ring of six carbon atoms by alternating single and double bonds with additional hydrogen atoms bonded to each carbon atom</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Biosphere</b> - the layer of Earth where all life exists, including the surface, atmosphere, and hydrosphere</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Colloidal solution</b> - a mixture in which a substance is suspended throughout another substance</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Cyclodiene</b> - an organic insecticide with a chlorinated methylene group creating a bridge across a 6-carbon ring</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Ex Situ</b> - Off site; at a different location</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Floc</b> - a lose clump of fine particles</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>In Situ</b> - On site; at the original location</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>K<sub>oc</sub> factor</b> - ratio octanol to water in a solution; the ability of a substance to move in soil (low K factor = high mobility; high K factor = low mobility)</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>K<sub>ow</sub> factor</b> - resistance to water (low K factor = very hydrophilic & “small bioconcentration factors for aquatic life”)</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>LD<sub>50</sub></b> - (lethal dose, 50%) a measurement to calculate the dose that would kill about 50% of the test population; values can vary due to the technique of contact, but listings on this website are specific to rats - other animals have differing values</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Lipophilic</b> - Tends to combine or dissolve with lipids/fats</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>organochlorine pesticides</b> - pesticides that are chlorinated hydrocarbons that act as mosquito and agricultural control (good pesticides); their main feature is at least one covalently-bonded chlorine atom</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>polychlorinated dibenzo-p-dioxins</b> - an extremely poisonous grouping of dioxins that are formed when organic material - mainly garbage and fossil fuels - is burned</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>ppm</b> - parts per million</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Partition</b> - distribution of a solute in 2 immiscible (non similar) mixtures which are in contact</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Pascal</b> - Newton per m<sup>2</sup></p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Rhizosphere</b> - soil directly influenced by a plant and its roots</p>
                    <p class="manrope font-weight-thin textsize-1em"><b>Soil organic matter</b> - component of soil consisting of plant and animal debris in any state of decomposition</p>
